wdi2-SE.PRM.PRS5.ZS.def: Persistence to grade 5 (percentage of cohort reaching grade 5) is the share of children enrolled in the first grade of primary school who eventually reach grade 5. The estimate is based on the reconstructed cohort method.
wdi2-SE.PRM.PRS5.ZS.name: Persistence to grade 5
wdi2-SE.PRM.PRS5.ZS.source: UNESCO Institute for Statistics (http://uis.unesco.org/). Data as of September 2020.
